parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, increased emissions, and potentially cause engine failure, which can result in costly repairs and even accidents.
symptoms: The engine oil level drops rapidly
the engine oil light comes on
the engine makes unusual noises
the engine emits excessive smoke
the vehicle leaves oil spots on the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked serpentine belt can cause the belt to break, leading to engine overheating, loss of power steering and brakes, and potentially causing engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The serpentine belt makes a loud squealing or chirping noise
the belt is visibly cracked or damaged
the engine overheats
the power steering and brakes fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A noisy exhaust system can be a sign of a more serious underlying issue, such as a leaking exhaust manifold or damaged muffler, which can lead to decreased fuel efficiency, increased emissions, and potentially cause engine failure.
symptoms: The exhaust system makes a loud rattling
hissing
or grinding noise
the exhaust pipe is leaking
the vehicle's performance is decreased.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine valve leak can cause the engine to run rough, decrease fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in costly repairs and even accidents.
symptoms: The engine runs rough
the engine misfires
the engine makes unusual noises
the engine oil level drops rapidly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause serious engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine temperature gauge is in the red zone
the engine overheats
the coolant level is low
the vehicle leaves coolant spots on the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing belt failure can cause serious engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine makes unusual noises
the engine runs rough
the engine misfires
the timing belt is visibly damaged or broken.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning exterior lights can reduce visibility, increase the risk of accidents, and lead to traffic violations.
symptoms: Left brake light malfunction
fast blinking of flasher when using left signal
failure of signal lights
cracked or leaked right rear tail light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent stalling and rough idle can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall unexpectedly, leading to accidents or stranding the driver. Additionally, rough idle can reduce fuel efficiency and increase emissions.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls intermittently
the engine idles rough
the vehicle hesitates or stumbles when accelerating
the engine makes unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty generator can cause the vehicle's electrical system to malfunction, leading to stalling, dim or flickering headlights, and other electrical issues.
symptoms: The generator squeals or makes unusual noises when running
the battery light on the dashboard comes on
the vehicle's electrical system malfunctions
the headlights dim or flicker.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty starter motor can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
the starter motor makes unusual noises or clicks
the starter motor does not engage when the key is turned.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the transmission shift selector can cause the vehicle to shift into the wrong gear or fail to shift, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stalling.
symptoms: The transmission shift selector is stuck or difficult to move
the transmission shifts into the wrong gear
the transmission fails to shift
the vehicle stalls or hesitates when shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer cable can cause the speedometer to malfunction, leading to inaccurate speed readings, which can affect vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: The speedometer needle is stuck or erratic
the speedometer reading is inaccurate
the speedometer is not functioning at all.
